===Noun===
'''quaternion'''

#A 4 dimensional [[complex number]] that consists of a real dimension and 3 imaginary ones (''i'', ''j'', ''k'') that are each a [[square root]] of -1.  They are commonly used in [[vector]] mathematics and 3 Dimensional games.  Quaternion multiplication is the most common technique used by mathematicians to avoid [[gimbal lock]] when rotating vectors.

